result.formatted_address: Hong Kong, Cheung Sha Wan, Castle Peak Road 454
result.name: Soi Eat Thai Cuisine

reviews.text: I came here for a late lunch today and the server was helpful for accommodating a vegetarian. The menus is in Chinese and English. The lunch sets are a good deal and tasty. I ordered some take away. The Thai food and Ice Tea is still not 100% like what you get in Thailand but not too bad.

The beef noodle in soup is a must try .. very tasty. Never have this in Hong Kong so far. Love that it comes with fried pig skin 😝

The snake platter is up to standard.  If the shrimp one can be a bit more chewy, it will be wonderful.  Like the spring roll a lot.  Very authentic Thai.

The lemongrass tea can have more favor.  Generally, don't expect to have this good taste in this area.  Worth trying.
Good Thai food restaurants. quite crowded during lunch time. Not too spicy.
So far so good

Very yummy and nice staff
Most dish are at reasonable price, other than the oyster and beef
